properties.description:
Email : nicolas@mealcanteen.com|mattspider@hotmail.com|romain.sayd@ecomail.bio
Event home : https://www.instagram.com/fridays.ff.france/|https://www.facebook.com/events/784874331882444/|https://www.facebook.com/events/821812371551265/|https://www.facebook.com/events/821812371551265/|https://twitter.com/FFFParis2019|Twitter|Instagram.com/busticaccia|https://share.icloud.com/photos/03LGglfjymubgg1GRODbOZaig|We, 13 9th graders of the Waldorf school of Verrieres le Buisson, saw on the web site map that there was a strike every week in front of Paris's city hall so we decided to go but when we arrived, there wasn't anybody. We were very disappointed and we thought that we were missing school for nothing. But we finally decided to walk to the National Assembly with our banners and strike even thought we were only 13en. On the way, people encouraged us and when we arrived at the National Assembly a group of around 20 policemen came to us and asked us to stay at a specific place to strike. Then the policemen called the police Administration and they asked us why we were striking and if our parents and our teachers knew about it. We talked to them for a while and they told us that we could contact them if we want to organise another strike and that they would make sure of our security. I think that when we strike the goal is to draw the most attention and to show why we were striking. From this point of view it was a success even thought we were only 13en.|https://www.facebook.com/events/1001111526755948/|https://www.facebook.com/events/821812371551265/|https://instagram.com/youthforclimatefr?igshid=13iy89zufzdtm|https://twitter.com/RobinJullian/status/1138398612076072960|https://www.mealcanteen.com|https://www.facebook.com/events/1240670739426961/permalink/1273849622775739/|https://m.rtl.be/info/1179811|Here a link with some pictures taken in this digital action https://www.facebook.com/events/550301325866256/permalink/554080178821704/ Here also a song https://www.facebook.com/events/550301325866256/permalink/554058592157196/ We also had an english speaking event that drew less people https://www.facebook.com/events/564963300819885/ (30 out of the 500) Quite a few actions seen on twitter on this day following our cooperation with FFF digital and Parents for future.
